Antisemitism and racism travel the same road, meeting at the intersection of hate. These “isms” are on the rise here and abroad. Those who believe in justice and human rights should not be confused. We must confront hate wherever it rears its ugly head. I choose to fight hate.

Antisemitism has a very specific definition that is clothed in hate. The word is an affront and offense when used indiscriminately to describe a difference of policy and/or critique of government. I am offended for all of us when that word is used to describe me.

My take: The world is not a better place when people who believe in peace and human rights are crushed.
